claim.claim-text:
1. A pump element for installation in a pump bore of a hydraulic block, the pump element comprising:
a pump piston;
a restoring spring for the pump piston;
an inlet valve with an inlet valve cap, the inlet valve cap having a high-pressure sealing portion;
a closing spring and a closing body disposed in the inlet valve;
a valve seat element that at least before installation of the pump element in the pump bore is connected to the pump piston by nonpositive engagement, and the high-pressure sealing portion rests with spring force reinforcement in an axial direction by the restoring spring on the valve seat element; and
centering means provided for centering the inlet valve cap relative to the valve seat element.
